description.narrative: This project is part of the Strategic Partnership (SP) on Lobby and Advocacy, with the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs. TheSP (2016-2020) provides funding for influencing work on three thematic areas: 1) Right to Food; 2) Greater Responsibility in Finance for Development; 3) Conflict and Fragility. The ambition of the SP is to achieve policy changes by governments and the private sector to the benefit of groups facing poverty and injustice, and to strengthen civil society#s capacity to demand for such change. TheSP is implemented by an Alliance consisting of Oxfam Novib and SOMO. This particular project entails the Alliance coordination to achieve the qualitative implementation of the SP as well as the delivery of the Alliance#s obligations towards the Netherlands Ministry of Foreign Affairs. It entails activities such as day-to-day coordination and communication with Oxfam country offices, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, SOMO, and other implementing parties, as well as reporting, linking andlearning. In this regard, the work delivered under this project contributes to a more strategic, efficient and effective partnership of Oxfam Novib and SOMO within the Alliance and with the Ministry.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib was founded in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Oxfam Novib is member of the Oxfam International confederation. Working together in the confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib's main office is based in The Netherlands, it supports the work of a network of local offices, the implementation of global projects, fundraising, campaigning and advocacy. Oxfam Novib’s the Hague office contributes towards this project’s implementation.
